African superstar, Ayodeji Ibrahim Balogun, popularly known as Wizkid, has said he would have loved to do music collaboration with late music legends, Bob Marley and Fela Anikulapo-Kuti. In a video clip that surfaced online on the 23rd April, Wizkid had a chat with sports brands, Puma & JD and answered questions about his life, style and his dream collab. Starboy talked about how fun it was growing up with 12 sisters, getting style inspiration from the street, whatever he sees around him basically. Grammy award-winning Wizzy noted that he’ll be dropping an album pretty soon, once he’s done recording. When eventually asked about his dream collab, Wizkid revealed that he would have love to do music with Afrobeat pioneer, Fela Anikulapo-Kuti and Reggae legend, Bob Marley but they are no more.